article.headline: Duquesne 24, Dayton 16
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Connor Dixon threw for two touchdowns and ran for another as Duquesne scored 14 unanswered fourth-quarter points to come from behind to beat Dayton 24-16 on Saturday. The game was tied 10-10 at halftime and Duquesne (2-1) trailed 16-10 after Nick Glavin kicked field goals of 40 and 27 yards for Dayton (3-1) in the second half. Dixon, who completed just 12 of 32 passes, rallied Duquesne. He gave the Dukes a 17-16 lead with an 11-yard touchdown pass to Alex Roberson that capped a seven-play, 72-yard drive with 8:09 left. Dayton drove 36 yards on 9 plays before Duquense blocked a punt and recovered at the Dayton 39. Seven plays later, Dixon scored on a 1-yard run and Duquesne led 24-16 with 1:18 left. Akeem Moore sealed the win for Duquesne when he intercepted Rob Florian's pass on the first play of Dayton's next possession. The Dukes then ran out the clock. Dixon finished with 230 yards passing and also threw a 43-yard touchdown pass to Michael Rasky to open the scoring in the first quarter. Florian completed 27 or 54 passes for 277 yards but also threw another interception, to Duquesne's Bill Poletti.
